issue.title: Disable transcoding video on server
issue.body:
I'm hosting this app on a very low-end server (Core 2 Duo CPU to be precisely), where every transcoding take such amount of time that it's not feasible. Also, due to issues with ISP, any HTTP/S uploads to the server are limited at 8-10 MBits per second, so every upload I make is already small enough. Transcoding videos server-side from 720p to 720p with a little lower bitrate isn't profitable, especially when transcoding happens at 0.2x speed.
Would be much appreciated if there was an option to disable transcoding altogether, embedding the original video (as some of services already doing this in such way).
